com.yworks.yfiles.graph

Class FolderNodeState

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yworks.yfiles.graph.FoldingLabelOwnerState
      • com.yworks.yfiles.graph.FolderNodeState

  • public final class FolderNodeState
extends FoldingLabelOwnerState
    A data container representing the collapsed state of a node.

    When the properties of the state are changed, these changes are reflected immediately in the Views.

    See Also:
    FoldingManager.getFolderNodeState(INode)

      • asNode

        public final INode asNode()
        Returns an INode instance which represents this folder node state.

        The returned node is not present in any graph but may be passed to IFoldingView.getViewItem(com.yworks.yfiles.graph.IModelItem) to get the node state's folder node in the folding view graph.

        Returns:
        An INode instance which represents this folder node state.

      • getFoldingPortState

        public final FoldingPortState getFoldingPortState(IPort masterPort)
        Provides access to the folding state of a master port.

        This method can be used to query the folding state of a port at the folder which is represented by this state.

        Parameters:
        masterPort - The master port for which the state should be returned.
        Returns:
        A state holder implementation of the masterPort, which reflects the port in the node's collapsed state.
        See Also:
        FoldingPortState.getStyle(), FoldingPortState.getLocationParameter()
